<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-11-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-11-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="76" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d76">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Denby</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 77.]</seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of
                                    State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>,
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-11-19"><hi rend="italic">November 19, 1894</hi></date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>Our minister Tokyo is advised that any direct overtures for peace made by
                        China to Japan through the American minister at Peking will be
                        considered.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>